obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE BENGAL LAND HOLDER’ ATTENDANCE ACT, 1 84 8`
  line `A CT N O. XX OF 184 8`
  line `Passed by the Governor General of India in Council on the 23d September 1848.`
  line `An Act for the establishment and maintenance of field boundary marks in the Presidency of`
  line Bombay.
  line `W HEREAS by sundry Regulations of the Bengal Code, provision is made for the imposition of a daily`
  line `fine, by the Board of Revenue or other authority exercising the powers of that Board, on any proprietor or`
  line `farmer of land subject to the provisions contained in the s aid several Regulations, who, when duly`
  line `summoned by the Collector or other Officer exercising the power of Collector, shall omit or refuse to`
  line `attend, or to cause his Officer or Agent to attend, or to furnish the accounts or documents required, and`
  line `shall no t shew sufficient cause for such omission; and it is further provided that the fine, when confirmed`
  line `by Government, is to be levied by same process as is prescribed for the recovery of arrears of revenue;`
  line `and whereas in many cases, by the delay thus occas ioned, the whole burden of the penalty is greatly`
  line `increased beyond what would be necessary, if summary power were given to the Officer by whom the`
  line `requisition is made, to impose and levy reasonable fines, subject to review by the Commissioner of`
  line `Revenue an d other superior authority, It is enacted as follows:`
  line `I. If any proprietor or farmer of land shall omit or refuse to attend, or to cause his Officer or Agent to`
  line `attend, when duly summoned by the Collector, in any case specified in any of the said Regulatio ns, by the`
  line `time prescribed in the notice issued by the Collector, or shall omit or refuse to furnish the accounts or`
  line `documents required, and shall not shew sufficient cause for such omission, the Collector may impose of`
  line `his own authority such daily fine, t o be payable daily until compliance with the requisition, as he may`
  line `think adequate to the situation and circumstances in life or the defaulter, not exceeding in any case the`
  line `daily fine of fifty Rupees: and the amount of such fine, accruing due from time to time may be levied`
  line `without further confirmation, by the same process as is prescribed for the recovery of arrears of revenue.`
  line `II. The Collector shall forthwith report the imposition of every such fine, and the amount thereof, and`
  line `also from time to time the amount levied, to the Commissioner of Revenue, who shall report the same for`
  line `the information of the local Government.`
  line `III. Every order passed by a Collector under this Act shall be appealable in the usual manner to the`
  line `Commissioner o f Revenue, and other superior authority; but no such appeal shall avail to prevent the`
  line `levy of any fine so imposed pending the appeal.`
  line `IV. Whenever the amount levied under any such order, issued for any default by authority of a`
  line `Collector under this Act, shall have exceeded five hundred Rupees, the Collector shall report the case`
  line `specially to the Commissioner of Revenue; and no further levy for such default shall be made otherwise`
  line `than by authority of the Commissioner of Revenue.`
  line `V. Nothing in this Act co ntained shall be deemed to repeal the power of imposing daily fines and of`
  line `levying the fines so imposed in the manner prescribed by the said several Regulations.`
  line `VI. The word “Collector” used in this Act shall be taken to mean any person lawfully exercisin g the`
  line `powers of a Collector.`
  line `VII. This Act shall not extend to the North West Provinces of the Presidency of Bengal.`
